INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '11a79592-5da4-4e7f-9980-1f7c5acd0490',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Grafana Dashboards — RED and USE Methods Side by Side$escape$,
  $escape$Grafana natively supports both RED (Rate, Errors, Duration) and USE (Utilization, Saturation, Errors) methods, and the key is knowing which panel belongs to which method. RED targets your services; USE targets your infrastructure resources.

For RED, wire three stat or time-series panels per service using Prometheus: `rate(http_requests_total[5m])` for rate, `rate(http_requests_total{status=~"5.."}[5m]) / rate(http_requests_total[5m])` for error ratio, and `histogram_quantile(0.99, rate(http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m]))` for p99 latency. Group these in a Grafana row per service and use `$service` template variables to fan out.

For USE, target node_exporter metrics: CPU utilization via `1 - avg(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}[5m]))`, saturation via `node_load1 / count(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"})`, and errors via `rate(node_disk_io_time_seconds_total[5m])`. Use Grafana's threshold bands (80%/90%) on gauge panels to make saturation immediately visible.

Combine both method rows in a single dashboard with a `datasource` variable so the same layout works across staging and production Prometheus instances without duplication.$escape$,
  $escape$// Grafana panel JSON model snippet — RED error ratio + USE CPU utilization
{
  "panels": [
    {
      "title": "RED — Error Ratio",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "targets": [{
        "expr": "rate(http_requests_total{status=~\"5..\", service=\"$service\"}[5m]) / rate(http_requests_total{service=\"$service\"}[5m])",
        "legendFormat": "error ratio"
      }]
    },
    {
      "title": "USE — CPU Utilization",
      "type": "gauge",
      "targets": [{
        "expr": "1 - avg(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode=\"idle\",instance=\"$instance\"}[5m]))",
        "legendFormat": "cpu util"
      }],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "thresholds": {
            "steps": [{"color": "green", "value": 0}, {"color": "yellow", "value": 0.8}, {"color": "red", "value": 0.9}]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
